100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 4, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and the need for disarmament following World War I. In the United States, the trial of the "Scopes Monkey Trial" continued to captivate the nation, as debates over evolution versus creationism took center stage in Tennessee. Meanwhile, in Britain, Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin faced mounting pressure regarding economic challenges and the state of the coal industry.
